race.comment: AGE OF GRACE (3) did her best work late to score this track/trip second up. She will be better for that and Pike stays aboard. Maps for a soft run and is well placed to repeat the dose. SIDE SHOW (6) was beaten a whisker at York first-up over 1500m and impressed belting home from the back. His overall figures stack up for this, and his second-up record is handy. Presents on a 7-day return and is a chance. SWEET TEA (4) was well-supported at Belmont 5 days ago but didn't get into it after settling back over shorter. She was beaten less than 2L at Belmont over this distance leading into that, and was a winner there the one before. Better suited and can get back on track. SNIP OF GOSSIP (7) didn't manage a wide gate heavily supported at Toodyay but had been narrowly beaten at Belmont first-up. Suited stepping up to the mile and jumps from an inside gate today. A chance at best.
